@Endnode
@Node "STP" "Starting the program"

@{b}@{u}Starting the program@{uu}@{ub}

WBJoyTest can be started from Workbench by double-clicking on its icon, or
from a Shell window by typing in its name (type in 'WBJoyTest ?' to see the
complete CLI template).

See @{"ToolTypes and CLI arguments" link "TCA"} for the program's settings.


@Endnode
@Node "TCA" "ToolTypes and CLI arguments"

@{b}@{u}ToolTypes and CLI arguments@{uu}@{ub}

WBJoyTest recognizes the following ToolTypes and CLI arguments:

   @{b}JOYSTICK=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies which joystick you want to test (1 or 2; default=2).

   @{b}XPOS=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s horizontal position.

   @{b}YPOS=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s vertical position.

   @{b}SAMPLESPATH=<path>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the path from which you want to load the
   samples. It must end with a slash (/) or colon (:) character.

   @{b}SND1=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   up (fire released).

   @{b}PER1=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND1' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND2=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   to the right (fire released).

   @{b}PER2=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND2' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND3=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   down (fire released).

   @{b}PER3=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND3' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND4=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   to the left (fire released).

   @{b}PER4=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND4' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND5=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   up (fire pressed).

   @{b}PER5=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND5' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND6=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   to the right (fire pressed).

   @{b}PER6=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND6' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND7=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   down (fire pressed).

   @{b}PER7=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND7' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').

   @{b}SND8=<name>@{ub}
   Specifies the name of the sample you want to play by moving the joystick
   to the left (fire pressed).

   @{b}PER8=<n>@{ub}
   Specifies the period (rate) for 'SND8' in the range 113 to 1200. The
   default value is 428 (middle 'C').


@Endnode
@Node "MAW" "The main window"

@{b}@{u}The main window@{uu}@{ub}

After you start the program, the main window appears. Move the joystick in all
the directions and press the fire button to test all the switches and play the
samples attached to them. To play the first 4 samples, move the joystick with
the fire button released, whereas to play the last 4 samples, move the
joystick with the fire button pressed. The window's title bar tells you which
joystick you are currently testing.


@Endnode
@Node "MEN" "The menu"

@{b}@{u}The menu@{uu}@{ub}

WBJoyTest provides the following menu:

   @{b}Project/Test joystick@{ub}
   Lets you choose which joystick you want to test (1 or 2).

   @{b}Project/About...@{ub}
   Shows some information about the program.

   @{b}Project/Quit@{ub}
   Quits the program.


@Endnode
@Node "NOT" "Notes"

@{b}@{u}Notes@{uu}@{ub}

   - The program is only able to load raw or non-compressed IFF-8SVX
     samples (one-shot or looped). Moreover, if a sample is longer than
     131000 bytes, it will be truncated.
   - You can also play the samples by pressing the numerical keys (1 to 8).
   - You can press the 'Esc' key to quit the program.


@Endnode
@Node "GUA" "Guarantee"

@{b}@{u}Guarantee@{uu}@{ub}

The program has been tested several times, but its reliability is not
guaranteed at 100%. I (@{"the author" link "AUT"}) do not consider myself responsible
for loss or damage of data as consequence of the use of the program. Use
WBJoyTest at your own risk.


@Endnode
