@Node "HIS" "History"

@{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

   1.0  - First release.

   1.1  - Added the 'XPOS', 'YPOS', 'SAMPLESPATH' and 'SND1..8'
          @{"ToolTypes and CLI arguments" link "TCA"}.
        - Added the 'Project' @{"menu" link "MEN"} containing the 'About...' and 'Quit'
          items.

   1.11 - The program did not work on 68000/68010 machines.
        - Now the program can play looped samples too.
        - Now the maximum sample length is 131000 bytes instead of 128000.
        - Now the program uses the dos.library ReadArgs() function to read
          the @{"CLI arguments" link "TCA"}.
        - Added the 'PER1..8' @{"ToolTypes and CLI arguments" link "TCA"}.
        - Now you can also play the samples by pressing the numerical keys (1
          to 8).

   1.12 - All the samples were by mistake played at the rate specified by the
          'PER4' @{"ToolType or CLI argument" link "TCA"}.
        - Now the @{"ToolTypes" link "TCA"} are read even if you change the program's
          name.
        - Added the 'JOYSTICK' @{"ToolType and CLI argument" link "TCA"}
        - Added the 'Test joystick' item to the 'Project' @{"menu" link "MEN"}.
        - Now you can press the 'Esc' key to quit the program.
        - Some other minor changes.


@Endnode
